Introduction: 
Winning an Academy Award is widely recognized as a marker of success in the film industry, often leading to higher salaries, 
greater visibility and demand, and increased prestige. Professional networks and repeated collaborations may also shape career advancement 
and recognition within Hollywood. This study explores the relationship between actor-director collaborations and award success.

